                            <comment id="14723" author="juergen.hoeller" created="Mon, 19 Sep 2005 02:23:54 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for pointing this out - we throw an OptimisticLockingFailureException for Hibernate&apos;s StaleStateException now. Hibernate 2.1 didn&apos;t have that super exception, hence that check never got added for the Hibernate3 support (which started as a port of the Hibernate 2.1 support)...&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Juergen&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
